<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1055" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄντην</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄντα</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">opposite, in front, in</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">to
            the face;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄντην ἵστασθε</span> (opp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φεύγειν</span>), <i><span class="en">Il.
            11.590</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἄντην βαλλομένων</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 12.152</span></i>; ‘in view,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 6.221</span></i>; with <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐναλίγκιος, εἰκέλη</span>, the effect of <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄντην</span> is largely that of emphasis, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.5</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 22.240</span></i>; so
          with <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὁμοιωθήμεναι</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.187</span></i>; ‘openly,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγαπαζέμεν ἄντην</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            24.464</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
